rComments: Okay for PSYC57 which is a neuroscience course she makes you do these stupid computer science assignments which has nothing to do with the course. She just finds it useful for students to learn this which I get but she makes the assignments so long and hard and there are 4 of them worth 8% each like wtf . THIS IS A PSYCHOLOGY COURSE not comp sci
She makes you work your ass off for any assignment that worths like %5 or %8, and there are many of those assignments from the 1st week!

The best professor I've had at this school. She cares so much about her students and provides very useful feedback to help you learn and improve, instead of just giving you a grade and not allowing you to grow. Phenomenal professor and a genuinely great person. I worked very hard but learned to push my limits to levels I didn't think I could!

She is a great and super nice prof who is extremely passionate about what she teaches and genuinely cares for her students. But, she's SO passionate that the content and work can be a bit too much at times. I did feel very overwhelmed throughout this class, but it's still very interesting and she teaches it well. If you have her, get ready to WORK.

On top of her dazziling resume and qualifications, Cendri is one the best psych profs at U of T because of her kindness, attention to her students, and her true passion for what she studies and teaches. Her course might not be everyone's favorite due to its difficulty but it will most certainly guarantee a fruitful learning experience! :)

rComments: This is meant to be a C level class but it is harder than my D level psych class. The readings are super hard. They barely make any sense. She covers a ton of content in her lectures then she adds more on top of it if she runs out of time. Then on top of all that we have assignments. The content of this class is equal to 3 D level classes! HELP!!!
Fair, accessible outside class, inspirational, clear grading criteria, amazing lecture  Exams are hard, get ready to read. Extra credit and tutorial are extremely helpful.

This Prof sets the standard, she knows her stuff and the course content is extremely interesting. With cognition thrown into the mix of social psychology it is more challenging but Prof offers 5% extra credit and is responsive to student feedback for exams. Research articles assigned weekly, lectures posted online, one highly structured paper

She's one of the smartest, most caring, and motivating lecturers I've had. Lectures are interesting and engaging. Inspired me for many research ideas. Exams are tough, because the material is not that easy, but this is evolving over time since she continuously takes feedback from students. Attendance is not a must but definitely recommended.
